34	        // with SameSite=Strict, which prevents cross-origin cookie attachment — the primary CSRF
35	        // vector for cookie-based tokens. Because the app is fully stateless (no server-side
36	        // session), standard CSRF mitigations that rely on session state do not apply. CSRF is
37	        // therefore disabled globally for all endpoints; the following defences are in place:
38	        //   1. SameSite=Strict cookie attribute on the refresh cookie — primary mitigation.
39	        //   2. Origin header validation in AuthApiController.validateOrigin() — called by the
40	        //      /api/auth/refresh and /api/auth/logout endpoints to reject requests whose Origin
41	        //      header does not match the server's own origin. This provides defence-in-depth
42	        //      for older browsers that may not enforce SameSite=Strict.
43	        //   3. Bearer-token pattern on all other API calls — an attacker cannot read the
44	        //      access token from a different origin, so forged requests fail authentication.
45	        http
